"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675461","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-26","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 25 October 2016 to Question 50276 to the hon. Member for East Renfrewshire (Mrs Oswald).</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-01-26T16:39:24.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675461/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675461/answer","20161031_WQnA_extract_50276_MOD_Staff.docx","20161031_WQnA_extract_50276_MOD_Staff.docx","50276 - WQnA extract on MOD Staff","50276 - WQnA extract on MOD Staff","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675461/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-19","Ministry of Defence: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many officials of his Department are working full-time on preparations for the UK leaving the EU; and what proportion of his Department's staff that number represents.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","60876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675462","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-27","<p>The number of compensation claims paid by the Ministry of Defence (MOD) for livestock in each of the last five years are:</p><p> </p><p>2012 - 34 Incidents £142,822.67</p><p>2013 - 37 Incidents £167,559.58</p><p>2014 - 32 Incidents £192,836.78</p><p>2015 - 25 Incidents £124,016.50</p><p>2016 - 18 Incidents £215,304.89</p><p> </p><p>As a comparison the number of claims paid by the MOD under the then Labour Government were:</p><p> </p><p>2006 - 63 Incidents £244,325.44</p><p>2007 - 90 Incidents £275,702.45</p><p>2008 - 80 Incidents £430,908.05</p><p>2009 - 63 Incidents £367,937.31</p><p> </p><p>A breakdown of the compensation paid in relation to each incident is attached.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-01-27T14:04:50.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675462/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675462/answer","60911 - Breakdown_of_compensation_paid_to_low_flying_incidents_involving_livestock.xlsx","60911 - Breakdown_of_compensation_paid_to_low_flying_incidents_involving_livestock.xlsx","60911 - Breakdown of compensation paid","60911 - Breakdown of compensation paid","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675462/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-19","Low Flying","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many low flying incidents involved livestock in each of the last five years; and what the cost was of compensation paid in relation to each of those incidents.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","60911"
