"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675464","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-26","<p>The Royal Navy use a variety of measures to encourage retention of military personnel with essential nuclear skills. These range from accelerated apprenticeship schemes, prioritising training opportunities, offering extensions of service, and the payment of targeted Financial Retention Incentives or Recruiting and Retention Pay.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-01-26T16:05:31.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675464/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675464/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675464/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-19","Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to ensure that defence personnel with essential nuclear skills are retained by the Royal Navy.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","60913"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675465","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-26","<p>The Job Advertisement for Chief Executive Officer (CEO) of the new Submarine Delivery Body closed on 23 January 2017. We will appoint the CEO as soon as the process allows. The operating cost budget for the new body has yet to be determined and Ministry of Defence (MOD) officials are working to ensure that an appropriate level of funding is provided to allow the Delivery Body to deliver its responsibilities effectively.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","60919","2017-01-26T16:04:17.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675465/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675465/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675465/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-19","Submarine Delivery Body","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he expects a permanent Chief Executive Officer of the new Submarine Delivery Body to be appointed.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","60914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675466","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-27","<p>The amount of compensation paid to Armed Forces personnel as a result of road traffic accidents in each of the last five calendar years is as follows:</p><p><strong>2012</strong></p><p>£1,373,064</p><p><strong>2013</strong></p><p>£1,731,330</p><p><strong>2014</strong></p><p>£530,732</p><p><strong>2015</strong></p><p>£4,707,070</p><p><strong>2016</strong></p><p>£1,301,073</p><p>The figures relate to common law claims brought by Armed Forces personnel against their employer, the Ministry of Defence (MOD). An example might be a soldier injured when travelling as a passenger in a MOD vehicle which is involved in an accident.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-01-27T14:30:05.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675466/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675466/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675466/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-19","Armed Forces: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much compensation his Department has paid to armed forces personnel as a result of road traffic accidents in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","60916"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675467","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-26","<p>The Ministry of Defence remains fully committed to its relationship with the wider defence industry and other Government Departments to ensure its people have the required nuclear skills. This includes membership and chairmanship of a number of skills forums alongside companies such as BAE Systems, Rolls-Royce, Babcock and the Atomic Weapons Establishment. Recent examples of this work include the Nuclear Skills Strategy which was published in December 2016, and the Building our Industrial Strategy green paper, published in January 2017.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-01-26T16:03:35.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675467/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675467/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675467/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-19","Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to ensure that the defence industry maintains the people with nuclear skills required for his Department's nuclear-based programmes.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","60917"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675468","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-26","<p>There are currently 1,400 bearskins in use/stock, all of which are accounted for. The requirement for new bearskins is kept to a minimum, with their procurement on-going based on need and the availability of material.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-01-26T16:06:53.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675468/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675468/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675468/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-19","Armed Forces: Furs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many bearskins are (a) in use and (b) unaccounted for; and whether he is taking steps to procure additional bearskins.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","60918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675469","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-26","<p>The Job Advertisement for Chief Executive Officer (CEO) of the new Submarine Delivery Body closed on 23 January 2017. We will appoint the CEO as soon as the process allows. The operating cost budget for the new body has yet to be determined and Ministry of Defence (MOD) officials are working to ensure that an appropriate level of funding is provided to allow the Delivery Body to deliver its responsibilities effectively.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","60914","2017-01-26T16:04:17.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675469/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675469/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675469/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-19","Submarine Delivery Body","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what budget has been allocated to the new Submarine Delivery Body.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","60919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675470","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-26","<p>Trade union members at the Atomic Weapons Establishment (AWE) have been undertaking industrial action since 14 November 2016 in relation to proposed changes to the AWE Pension Scheme by AWE plc. Robust measures are in place to manage any impact of this industrial action.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-01-26T16:05:00.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675470/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675470/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675470/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-19","AWE: Industrial Disputes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the effect of the recent industrial action by Atomic Weapons Establishment staff on the delivery of his Department's nuclear weapons programme.","false","Biography information for Kirsten Oswald","East Renfrewshire","Kirsten  Oswald","60871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675471","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-01-24","<p>The Ministry of Defence Art Collection currently comprises 2,145 items of fine art, prints, maps, photographs, manuscripts, sculptures, antique furniture, antique clocks and chronometers. The items are located in various locations across the Defence Estate, other Government Departments, museums and other public bodies. Further to the Written Ministerial Statement made on 12 May 2016, (HCWS720) work is progressing well to transfer ownership of the most significant works within the collection to other public institutions to ensure their continued protection and public display.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-01-24T15:33:27.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675471/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675471/answer","Hansard Extract 12 May 2016, HCWS720.docx","Hansard Extract 12 May 2016, HCWS720.docx","Art  Collection","Art  Collection","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675471/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-01-19","Ministry of Defence: Art Works","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many works of art his Department owns and where they are located.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","60832"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675472","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-24","<p>The Civil Aviation Authority has a record of the following number of such incidents which were logged on its mandatory occurrence reporting (MOR) database:</p><p> </p><p>2010 One</p><p> </p><p>2011 to 2016 Nil</p><p> </p><p>It is possible that some other incidents may not have been considered as an MOR.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-24T16:13:21.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675472/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675472/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675472/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-01-19","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many foreign military aircraft have made unapproved landings at UK airports and airfields since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","60833"
