"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675520","Department of Health","false","2017-01-27","<p>The new infected blood payment scheme will contain a discretionary element.</p><p> </p><p>The three existing discretionary schemes will remain in place until the new scheme administrator is in place later in 2017. This will ensure a smooth handover of the discretionary elements under the new scheme.</p><p> </p><p>Further details of the discretionary support scheme will be provided in advance of the new scheme being set up.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-01-27T12:01:39.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675520/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675520/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675520/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Blood: Contamination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what progress has been made on incorporating current discretionary support payments into the new scheme for victims of contaminated blood; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Alistair Burt","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","60813"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675521","Department of Health","false","2017-01-24","<p>The Department does not hold this information centrally.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-01-24T11:26:35.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675521/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675521/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675521/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Suicide: Mothers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many mothers died by suicide within a year after the birth of their child in (a) 2015 and (b) 2016.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","60839"
