"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675524","Department of Health","false","2017-01-24","<p>The information requested is not available centrally.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England collects the number of elective operations cancelled at the ‘last minute’ for non-clinical reasons on a quarterly basis. It does not collect the total number of cancelled operations, a breakdown of the type of operations that have been cancelled, or the specific reason for the cancellation. Operations cancelled for clinical reasons are not collected as the patient is not available for the operation. A last minute cancellation is defined as when a patient’s operation is cancelled by the hospital on or after the day of admission (including the day of surgery) for non-clinical reasons. The collection does not therefore capture elective operations cancelled or rearranged with more notice.</p><p> </p><p>Quarter 3 2016/17 data, January to March 2017, will be published in May 2017.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-01-24T13:44:49.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675524/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675524/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675524/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Cancer: Surgery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many cancer patients have had their operation cancelled due to a shortage of beds in each month since January 2016.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","60846"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675525","Department of Health","false","2017-01-27","<p>In 2016/17, NHS England funded local health economies with a total of £1,474,500 to support implementation activities and costs relating to the NHS Diabetes Prevention Programme (NHS DPP). Health economies are partnerships of clinical commissioning groups and local authorities.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has also nationally commissioned the NHS DPP behavioural interventions that are provided to local health economies.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-01-27T11:44:49.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675525/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675525/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675525/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Diabetes: Health Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, which clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) have received funding under the NHS Diabetes Prevention Programme; and how much funding each of those CCGs received.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","60779"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675526","Department of Health","false","2017-01-27","<p>To establish the information requested back to the start of the currently-constituted Department in 1988 would incur disproportionate costs. This cost would be high because the process would require the manual retrieval and reading of archived paper files and recourse to archived but discontinued electronic storage systems. It should also be noted that older paper files may have been subject to phased destruction.</p><p> </p><p>The relevant information available back to 2010 is provided below:</p><p> </p><p>Since 2010, nine individual members of the senior civil service have been absent from work due to mental health reasons on ten different occasions. The specific months in which these absences occurred are not given to avoid identifying the individual officers concerned.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is committed to reducing work-related absence due to mental illness and has a number of services in place to support members of staff suffering from such conditions. To this end the Department:</p><p> </p><p>- Delivers two day Mental Health First Aid training courses in London and Leeds; and half-day Mental Health First Aid Lite courses;</p><p>- Supports and promotes a network of Mental Health First Aiders;</p><p>- Delivers Tackling Stress at Work courses using the Health and Safety Executive’s Management Standards framework;</p><p>- Signposts staff to courses on mental health that are available through Civil Service Learning; and</p><p>- Delivers an programme of events around World Mental Health Day in October, which this year included pledge boards across the Departmental estate and tea and talk sessions.</p><p> </p><p>The Department also provides access to an Employment Assistance Programme, which is advertised to staff via the intranet. It promotes The Charity for Civil Servants, whose services include a mental health helpline and signposts to MIND, the Samaritans and internal staff networks where staff can get help and assistance.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-01-27T14:36:01.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675526/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675526/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675526/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Department of Health: Sick Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many senior civil servants in his Department were on a leave of absence from work due to mental illness in each month of each year since the Department's creation.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","60802"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675527","Department of Health","false","2017-01-24","<p>The NHS Diabetes Prevention Programme (NHS DPP) is for individuals diagnosed as high risk of type 2 diabetes, with a high blood sugar recorded in the past 12 months either through a National Health Service health check or other means. NHS DPP does not test for diabetes but rather offers support to those at risk of type 2 diabetes.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-01-24T16:24:27.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675527/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675527/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675527/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Diabetes: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people have been tested for diabetes under the NHS Diabetes Prevention Programme.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","60810"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675528","Department of Health","false","2017-01-27","<p>NHS England set Clinical Commissioning Group (CCG) allocations and the figures for Leicester City CCG for 2014-15, 2015-16 and 2016-17, the current financial year, can be found on NHS England’s website, and are as set out in the following links:</p><p> </p><p>2014-15 allocations:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/ccg-allocation-big-table-v2.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/ccg-allocation-big-table-v2.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>2015-16 allocations:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/annx-b-ccg-allctns.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/annx-b-ccg-allctns.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>2016-17 allocations:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/ccg-allocations.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/ccg-allocations.pdf</a></p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-01-27T12:21:36.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675528/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675528/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675528/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Leicester City Clinical Commissioning Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the budget for Leicester City Clinical Commissioning Group (a) was in 2014-15, (b) was in 2015-2016 and (c) is for the current financial year.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","60811"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675529","Department of Health","false","2017-01-24","<p>The Department does not receive any funding for projects from the Conflict Stability and Security Fund.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-01-24T12:05:16.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675529/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675529/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675529/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Department of Health: Conflict, Stability and Security Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what projects by (a) name and (b) value his Department funded from the Conflict Stabilisation and Security Fund; and which of those projects were categorised as contributing towards Overseas Development Aid.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","60806"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675530","Department of Health","false","2017-01-27","<p>In the 2016-17 Mandate to Health Education England (HEE), the Government tasked HEE with taking forward the relevant recommendations set out in the Independent Cancer Task Force’s report ‘Achieving World Class Cancer Outcomes: a strategy for England 2015-2020’, including to work with partners to develop a vision for the future shape and skills mix of the workforce required to deliver a modern, holistic patient-centred cancer service.</p><p> </p><p>The strategic review includes a baseline of the current cancer related workforce; a review of the current skills mix; and a strategy for working with Cancer Alliances and Local Workforce Action Boards to find solutions for workforce challenges as new models of service delivery emerge.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-01-27T13:58:38.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675530/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675530/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675530/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what Health Education England is required to deliver in March 2017 to satisfy the mandate for a strategic review of the cancer workforce.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","60759"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675531","Department of Health","false","2017-01-27","<p>Ministers regularly meet with Health Education England (HEE) to discuss workforce matters, including the progress it has made on its commitment to deliver a workforce with the right skills and competences to deliver high-quality modern cancer services.</p><p> </p><p>Departmental officials also regularly meet with HEE as a member of the National Cancer Transformation Board, the group which has been tasked with overseeing the implementation of the 2015 Cancer Strategy for England.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-01-27T13:59:46.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675531/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675531/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675531/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions Ministers of his Department have had with Health Education England on the strategic review of the cancer workforce in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","60764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675532","Department of Health","false","2017-01-24","<p>The Care Quality Commission (CQC) continues to monitor the progress of Marie Stopes International (MSI) very closely and plans to inspect its centres and United Kingdom administrative offices again in the near future to ensure that ongoing improvements are made and maintained. The CQC has made clear that they will not hesitate to take further action, if necessary, in order to guarantee MSI meets the standard of care they expect and that its patients deserve. MSI is addressing the issues raised, including the management of fetal remains.</p><p> </p><p>The Department continues to monitor the situation with particular regard being had to the statutory approval responsibilities of the Secretary of State.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","60716","2017-01-24T16:21:33.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675532/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675532/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675532/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to the findings of the report from the Care Quality Commission on Marie Stopes International, published in December 2016, what steps his Department plans to put in place to ensure that fetal remains are disposed of by private abortion clinics respectfully and in accordance with the wishes of patients who have undergone abortions.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","60714"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675533","Department of Health","false","2017-01-24","<p>There have been no meetings between Departmental Ministers and representatives of Unicef Baby Friendly, during the period of 1 January 2016 and 20 January 2017.</p><p> </p><p>Departmental officials attended three meetings where representatives of Unicef Baby Friendly were present. These meetings took place on 5 July 2016, 28 July 2016 and 15 December 2016.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-01-24T11:59:58.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675533/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675533/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675533/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","UNICEF","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many times and on which dates (a) Ministers and (b) officials of his Department have met with representatives of Unicef Baby Friendly.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","60720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675534","Department of Health","false","2017-01-24","<p>Our records indicate that from January 2016 to January 2017, Ministers had no meetings with First Steps Nutrition Trust and Baby Milk Action either separately or together.</p><p> </p><p>In the same period, officials had one meeting with both organisations on 3 August 2016.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","60722","2017-01-24T12:06:49.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675534/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675534/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675534/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","First Steps Nutrition Trust","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many times and on which dates (a) Ministers and (b) officials of his Department have met with representatives of First Steps Nutrition Trust.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","60721"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675535","Department of Health","false","2017-01-24","<p>Our records indicate that from January 2016 to January 2017, Ministers had no meetings with First Steps Nutrition Trust and Baby Milk Action either separately or together.</p><p> </p><p>In the same period, officials had one meeting with both organisations on 3 August 2016.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","60721","2017-01-24T12:06:49.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675535/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675535/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675535/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Baby Milk Action","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many times and on which dates (a) Ministers and (b) officials of his Department have met with representatives of Baby Milk Action.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","60722"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675536","Department of Health","false","2017-01-27","<p>The Ministerial team have not met with representatives of Live Nation. Information on whether officials have met Live Nation could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-01-27T14:01:40.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675536/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675536/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675536/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Live Nation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many times and on which dates (a) Ministers and (b) officials of his Department have met with representatives of Live Nation.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","60723"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675537","Department of Health","false","2017-01-27","<p>The Ministerial team have not met with representatives of MG Alba. Information on whether officials have met MG Alba could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-01-27T13:55:06.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675537/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675537/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675537/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","MG Alba","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many times and on which dates (a) Ministers and (b) officials of his Department have met with representatives of MG Alba.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","60724"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675538","Department of Health","false","2017-01-24","<p>No decision has been made to close the congenital heart disease service at the Royal Brompton and Harefield NHS Foundation Trust.</p><p> </p><p>The congenital heart disease standards agreed by the NHS England Board in July 2015 include sub-categories that cover both research and using a network approach. The standards have been designed to support a continued collaborative approach to develop and sustain research and good practice.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","60728","2017-01-24T13:48:30.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675538/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675538/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675538/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Royal Brompton Hospital","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on the internationally recognised adult congenital heart disease research team at the Royal Brompton Hospital as a result of the proposed closure of congenital heart disease services at that hospital.","false","Biography information for Sarah Olney","Richmond Park","Sarah Olney","60727"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675539","Department of Health","false","2017-01-27","<p>No decision has been made on the proposals made by NHS England in July 2016. The proposal for the Royal Brompton and Harefield Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust is to decommission as a level 1 provider, not to close the congenital heart disease (CHD) service.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has been working with expert clinicians, patients, and Trust executives since 2013 to devise and agree a new set of standards for the treatment of CHD. The aim of these standards is to secure the best outcomes for all patients, including:</p><p> </p><p>- improved opportunities for survivors to lead better lives;</p><p>- tackling variation in services, particularly to ensure resilient 24-hour, seven days a week care; and</p><p>- improved patient experience.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England will be analysing the feedback from consultation to inform the NHS England Board’s decision-making later.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-01-27T11:29:01.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675539/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675539/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675539/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Royal Brompton Hospital","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will publish the cost-benefit analysis on the extent of the (a) improvements in clinical outcomes and (b) unit cost reductions anticipated to result from the proposed closure of congenital heart disease services at the Royal Brompton Hospital.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","60725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675540","Department of Health","false","2017-01-24","<p>No decision has been made to close the congenital heart disease service at the Royal Brompton and Harefield NHS Foundation Trust.</p><p> </p><p>The congenital heart disease standards agreed by the NHS England Board in July 2015 include sub-categories that cover both research and using a network approach. The standards have been designed to support a continued collaborative approach to develop and sustain research and good practice.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","60727","2017-01-24T13:48:30.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675540/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675540/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675540/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Royal Brompton Hospital","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment NHS England has made of the effect of the proposed dispersal of the Royal Brompton Hospital's congenital heart disease research team on care quality.","false","Biography information for Sarah Olney","Richmond Park","Sarah Olney","60728"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675541","Department of Health","false","2017-01-26","<p>NHS England still intends to publish initial findings from the Review this winter.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-01-26T13:09:59.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675541/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675541/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675541/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Paediatrics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether the initial findings of the NHS England paediatric critical care and specialised surgery in children service review are still expected to be published in winter 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","60726"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675542","Department of Health","false","2017-01-24","<p>The Care Quality Commission (CQC) continues to monitor the progress of Marie Stopes International (MSI) very closely and plans to inspect its centres and United Kingdom administrative offices again in the near future to ensure that ongoing improvements are made and maintained. The CQC has made clear that they will not hesitate to take further action, if necessary, in order to guarantee MSI meets the standard of care they expect and that its patients deserve. MSI is addressing the issues raised, including the management of fetal remains.</p><p> </p><p>The Department continues to monitor the situation with particular regard being had to the statutory approval responsibilities of the Secretary of State.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","60714","2017-01-24T16:21:33.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675542/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675542/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675542/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether he has made an assessment of the implications of the findings of the Care Quality Commission's report of 20 December 2016 on Marie Stopes International for (a) patient safety and (b) public confidence in private abortion clinics; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","60716"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675543","Department of Health","false","2017-01-24","<p>Whilst there is already evidence of the impacts of air pollution on health, and ongoing work to quantify these impacts, the associated costs to the National Health Service and social care budget are less understood. Public Health England (PHE) has commissioned a consortium led by the UK Health Forum to carry out a project on the estimation of costs to the NHS and social care due to the health impacts of air pollution as part of PHE’s Health Economics Commissioning Framework. The aim is to enable air pollution to be assessed against other public health threats and to support the strategic priority setting process.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-01-24T12:01:57.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675543/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675543/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675543/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Air Pollution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent estimate he has made of the cost to the NHS of treatment of people affected by air pollution and poor air quality.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","60718"
