"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675545","Department of Health","false","2017-01-24","<p>Our records indicate that from January 2016 to January 2017, Ministers had no meetings with the British Specialist Nutrition Association (BSNA).</p><p> </p><p>In the same period, officials had five meetings with the BSNA on the following dates:</p><p> </p><p>- 12 January 2017;</p><p>- 10 November 2016;</p><p>- 16 May 2016;</p><p>- 29 April 2016; and</p><p>- 18 February 2016.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-01-24T16:25:42.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675545/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675545/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675545/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","British Specialist Nutrition Association","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many times and on which dates (a) Ministers and (b) officials of his Department have met with representatives of the British Specialist Nutrition Association.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","60719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675546","Department of Health","false","2017-01-24","<p>There were 196,692 finished hospital admission episodes with a primary diagnosis for urinary tract infections in England in 2015/16.</p><p> </p><p>Replies to the hon. Member of Hornsey and Wood Green’s recent letters on urinary tract infections should be sent on or before Friday 27 January 2017.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","60732","2017-01-24T17:15:15.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675546/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675546/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675546/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Urinary Tract Infections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many patients have been diagnosed with chronic urinary tract infections over the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","60731"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675547","Department of Health","false","2017-01-24","<p>There were 196,692 finished hospital admission episodes with a primary diagnosis for urinary tract infections in England in 2015/16.</p><p> </p><p>Replies to the hon. Member of Hornsey and Wood Green’s recent letters on urinary tract infections should be sent on or before Friday 27 January 2017.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","60731","2017-01-24T17:15:15.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675547/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675547/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675547/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-19","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he plans to respond to the letters from the hon. Member for Hornsey and Wood Green of (a) 7 November and (b) 14 December 2016 on scheduling a meeting to discuss his Department's policy on the treatment of chronic urinary tract infections.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","60732"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675548","Home Office","false","2017-01-24","<p>Technical changes have already been made to the online booking system for Tehran in order to prevent abuse of the system. We continue to work with IT experts to further improve our systems and respond to emerging challenges.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-24T14:00:49.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675548/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675548/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675548/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-19","Visas: Iran","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to develop anti-bot technology to prohibit bulk booking of appointments in respect of VFS Global visa applications in the Republic of Iran.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","60755"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675549","Home Office","false","2017-01-25","<p>I am sorry but the Home Office does not hold the information requested<em>.</em></p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-25T16:47:42.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675549/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675549/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675549/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-19","Visas: Iran","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will publish data on the levels of non-compliance of visa conditions granted to Iranian nationals visiting the UK in each year since 2012.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","60744"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675550","Home Office","false","2017-01-30","<p>Asylum interview and decisions are undertaken by civil servants and not by Immigration Officers.</p><p> </p><p>All Asylum decision-making staff receive training that involves a dedicated five week course (or ‘Foundation Training programme’) which covers Asylum legislation, the Refugee Convention, Human Rights law, UK Immigration Rules and legislation, gender issues, modern slavery, Female Genital Mutilation, Lesbian, Gay and Bisexual claims and domestic violence as well as training on conducting asylum interviews and decisions.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-30T14:40:07.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675550/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675550/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675550/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-19","Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what training and advice is available to immigration officers carrying out asylum interviews where a claimant has been a victim of sexual violence.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","60741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675551","Home Office","false","2017-01-24","<p>The latest available Home Office immigration statistics of British citizenship applications, grants and refusals are published in ‘Immigration Statistics, July to September 2016’, available from the Home Office website at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-statistics</a> . Quarterly statistics covering the period in question are held here. Data for October to December 2016 will be published on 23 February 2017.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-24T14:02:13.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675551/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675551/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675551/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-19","Naturalisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many applications for naturalisation as a British citizen were (a) lodged, (b) granted and (c) refused in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","60742"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675552","Home Office","false","2017-01-24","<p>I am sorry but the data requested could only be provided at disproportionate cost by examination of individual records.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-24T13:18:03.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675552/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675552/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675552/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-19","Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many asylum applications that included medical evidence of torture her Department received in each of the last five years; and how many of those applications that were rejected were subsequently overturned on appeal.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","60735"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675553","Home Office","false","2017-01-27","<p>The number of Senior Civil Servants in the Home Office who were on a leave of absence from work due to mental illness since January 2010 is set out in the table below.</p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2"><p> </p></td><td colspan="7"><p><strong>Headcount %</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Grade Equivalency</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Reporting Group - Cabinet Office</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Senior Civil Servants</p></td><td><p>Mental Health Issues</p></td><td><p>0.0%</p></td><td><p>0.8%</p></td><td><p>1.5%</p></td><td><p>0.4%</p></td><td><p>0.0%</p></td><td><p>0.3%</p></td><td><p>1.4%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="9"><p><strong>Source</strong>: Data View - Office for National Statistics compliant monthly snapshot corporate Human Resources data for Home Office.</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="9"><p><strong>Period Covered</strong>: 1st January to 31st December in each year.</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="9"><p><strong>Extraction Date</strong>: 1st January of the following year.</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="9"><p><strong>Organisational Coverage</strong>: Figures include Home Office.</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="9"><p><strong>Employee Coverage</strong>: Data is based on headcount of all senior civil servants who were current at 31st December in each year and 12 months leavers, and had a leave of absence due to mental health issues during the period.</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="9"><p><strong>Senior Civil Servants</strong> are senior staff who undertake roles within SCS Pay Band 1, SCS Pay Band 2 and SCS Pay Band 3 along with the Permanent Secretary.</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="9"><p><strong>Note</strong>: Due to the small numbers involved we have provided the numbers per year rather than for individual months.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>In the Home Office we are committed to breaking down barriers and reducing stigma for those staff living with mental health conditions. We signed up to the Time to Change pledge in 2014 making a public commitment to be at the forefront of UK employers to tackle mental health issues in the workplace and we remain dedicated to ensuring mental health is a priority.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-01-27T14:58:25.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675553/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675553/answer","PQ 60775 Table 1 Final V2.xlsx","PQ 60775 Table 1 Final V2.xlsx","Table - PQ 60775","Table - PQ 60775","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675553/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-19","Home Office: Sick Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many senior civil servants in her Department were on a leave of absence from work due to mental illness in each month since January 2010.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","60775"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675554","Home Office","false","2017-01-24","<p>The Daniel Morgan Independent Panel has advised that it expects to finalise its report in 2017, but that this timetable remains under review. Once the Independent Panel presents its final report to the Home Secretary, arrangements will be made for its publication to Parliament.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-01-24T16:19:04.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675554/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675554/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/675554/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-01-19","Daniel Morgan Independent Panel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when she expects the report of the Daniel Morgan Independent Panel to be released.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","60845"
